extremePortLoadshareTable.name: extremePortLoadshareTable
extremePortLoadshareTable.description: A table of bindings between a master port and its load-sharing slaves: create/delete entries here to add/delete a port to/from a load-sharing group. Default is empty table. There are restrictions on what row creates will be accepted by each device - see Summit release notes for details.

extremePortLoadshareEntry.name: extremePortLoadshareEntry
extremePortLoadshareEntry.description: A binding between a master port and one of its load-sharing slave ports.

extremePortLoadshareMasterIfIndex.name: extremePortLoadshareMasterIfIndex
extremePortLoadshareMasterIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the port controlling a loadsharing group of ports which includes extremePortLoadshareSlaveIfIndex.

extremePortLoadshareSlaveIfIndex.name: extremePortLoadshareSlaveIfIndex
extremePortLoadshareSlaveIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the port which is a member of a loadsharing group controlled by extremePortLoadshareMasterIfIndex.

extremePortLoadshareGrouping.name: extremePortLoadshareGrouping
extremePortLoadshareGrouping.description: The Grouping value which identifies if load sharing is in pair or quad.

extremePortLoadshareStatus.name: extremePortLoadshareStatus
extremePortLoadshareStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

extremePortSummitlinkTable.name: extremePortSummitlinkTable
extremePortSummitlinkTable.description: A table of Extreme link configuration and status information. Contains a row for only those ports that are capable of operating in Summitlink-mode.

extremePortSummitlinkEntry.name: extremePortSummitlinkEntry
extremePortSummitlinkEntry.description: Link configuration and status information for a Summitlink Port.

extremePortSummitlinkAdminMode.name: extremePortSummitlinkAdminMode
extremePortSummitlinkAdminMode.description: Configurable operating mode for this Summitlink port. Configure to summitlinkOnly(1) before connecting this port to a SummitVC device.

extremePortSummitlinkState.name: extremePortSummitlinkState
extremePortSummitlinkState.description: Current status of a Summitlink link. Where a port has redundant PMD capability, this indicates up if either of the PMDs has an active link.

extremePortSummitlinkRejectReason.name: extremePortSummitlinkRejectReason
extremePortSummitlinkRejectReason.description: If a Summitlink connection has been attempted and failed to reach the up(1) state, this indicates the potential source of the failure.

extremePortLoadshare2Table.name: extremePortLoadshare2Table

extremePortLoadshare2Entry.name: extremePortLoadshare2Entry
extremePortLoadshare2Entry.description: A binding between a master port and one of its load-sharing slave ports.

extremePortLoadshare2MasterIfIndex.name: extremePortLoadshare2MasterIfIndex
extremePortLoadshare2MasterIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the port controlling a loadsharing group of ports which includes extremePortLoadshareSlaveIfIndex.

extremePortLoadshare2SlaveIfIndex.name: extremePortLoadshare2SlaveIfIndex
extremePortLoadshare2SlaveIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the port which is a member of a loadsharing group controlled by extremePortLoadshare2MasterIfIndex.

extremePortLoadshare2Algorithm.name: extremePortLoadshare2Algorithm
extremePortLoadshare2Algorithm.description: This value identifies the load sharing algorithm to be used for this group of load shared ports.

extremePortLoadshare2Status.name: extremePortLoadshare2Status
extremePortLoadshare2Status.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

extremePortRateShapeTable.name: extremePortRateShapeTable
extremePortRateShapeTable.description: A list of ports that have ingress rate limiting enforced.

extremePortRateShapeEntry.name: extremePortRateShapeEntry
extremePortRateShapeEntry.description: An entry that is either a rate limited or a loopback port. Any vlan that has rate limited ports should have one loopback port defined. The traffic parameters for the rate limited ports correspond to those that are defined for the loopback port in the extremePerPortQosTable.

extremePortRateShapePortType.name: extremePortRateShapePortType
extremePortRateShapePortType.description: Whether a loopback or rate limited port.

extremePortRateShapeLoopbackTag.name: extremePortRateShapeLoopbackTag
extremePortRateShapeLoopbackTag.description: An unique internal tag that will needs to be set up for the vlan corresponding to this entry for adding ingress rate limited ports to the corresponding vlan.

extremePortRateShapeStatus.name: extremePortRateShapeStatus
extremePortRateShapeStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

extremePortUtilizationTable.name: extremePortUtilizationTable
extremePortUtilizationTable.description: Global Qos Profiles are defined in the extremeQosProfileTable. This table contains a list of ports for which certain QoS parms are reported.

extremePortUtilizationAvgTxBw.name: extremePortUtilizationAvgTxBw
extremePortUtilizationAvgTxBw.description: The reported average bandwidth in the txmit direction. When displayed it shows as an Integer value i.e 99.99% is displayed as 9999.

extremePortUtilizationAvgRxBw.name: extremePortUtilizationAvgRxBw
extremePortUtilizationAvgRxBw.description: The reported average bandwidth in the receive direction. When displayed it shows as an Integer value i.e 99.99% is displayed as 9999.

extremePortUtilizationPeakTxBw.name: extremePortUtilizationPeakTxBw
extremePortUtilizationPeakTxBw.description: The reported peak bandwidth in the txmit direction. When displayed it shows as an Integer value i.e 99.99% is displayed as 9999.

extremePortUtilizationPeakRxBw.name: extremePortUtilizationPeakRxBw
extremePortUtilizationPeakRxBw.description: The reported peak bandwidth in the receive direction. When displayed it shows as an Integer value i.e 99.99% is displayed as 9999.

extremePortInfoTable.name: extremePortInfoTable
extremePortInfoTable.description: This table contains a list of port information.

extremePortInfoFilterUpCounter.name: extremePortInfoFilterUpCounter
extremePortInfoFilterUpCounter.description: The reported Port Filter up counter value. This counter indicates the number of times a port's link state has transitioned from DOWN to UP state.

extremePortInfoFilterDownCounter.name: extremePortInfoFilterDownCounter
extremePortInfoFilterDownCounter.description: The reported Port Filter down counter value. This counter indicates the number of times a port's link state has transitioned from UP to DOWN state.

extremePortXenpakVendorTable.name: extremePortXenpakVendorTable
extremePortXenpakVendorTable.description: A table of Extreme Xenpak Module Vendor Name and type information. Contains a row for only those ports that are part of Xenpak module .

extremePortXenpakVendorEntry.description: Vendor name and type for Xenpak module.

extremePortXenpakVendorName.name: extremePortXenpakVendorName
extremePortXenpakVendorName.description: A human-readable string representing Vendor name of this module. This string should be the same for all entries having the same Xenpak module: this entry may not be modified.

extremePortIngressStatsPortTable.name: extremePortIngressStatsPortTable
extremePortIngressStatsPortTable.description: Port ingress statistics are returned for ports which support ingress queuing. This table contains a list of counters for each port.

extremePortIngressStatsLinkStatus.name: extremePortIngressStatsLinkStatus
extremePortIngressStatsLinkStatus.description: The current status of the link. Ready indicates the port is ready to accept a link; Active indicates the link is present at this port; Disabled shows that the link is disabled at this port; Not Present means the link is not present at this port.

extremePortIngressStatsPortHighPriBytes.name: extremePortIngressStatsPortHighPriBytes
extremePortIngressStatsPortHighPriBytes.description: The sum of all per queue CIR counts for this port, which indicates the bytes forwarded for high-priority packets.

extremePortIngressStatsPortLowPriBytes.name: extremePortIngressStatsPortLowPriBytes
extremePortIngressStatsPortLowPriBytes.description: The sum of all per queue PR counts for this port, which indicates the bytes forwarded for low-priority packets.

extremePortIngressStatsPortDroppedBytes.name: extremePortIngressStatsPortDroppedBytes
extremePortIngressStatsPortDroppedBytes.description: The total number of bytes dropped for this port.

extremePortIngressStatsTxXoff.name: extremePortIngressStatsTxXoff
extremePortIngressStatsTxXoff.description: The number of XOFF Flow Control packets sent from this port due to receive traffic congestion.

extremePortIngressStatsQueueTable.name: extremePortIngressStatsQueueTable
extremePortIngressStatsQueueTable.description: Port ingress statistics are returned for ingress queues. This table contains a list of counters for each ingress queue.

extremePortIngressStatsQueueHighPriBytes.name: extremePortIngressStatsQueueHighPriBytes
extremePortIngressStatsQueueHighPriBytes.description: The sum of all per queue CIR counts for this queue, which indicates the bytes forwarded for high-priority packets.

extremePortIngressStatsQueueLowPriBytes.name: extremePortIngressStatsQueueLowPriBytes
extremePortIngressStatsQueueLowPriBytes.description: The sum of all per queue PR counts for this queue, which indicates the bytes forwarded for low-priority packets.

extremePortIngressStatsQueuePercentDropp.name: extremePortIngressStatsQueuePercentDropped
extremePortIngressStatsQueuePercentDropp.description: The percentage of receive bytes dropped by this queue relative to the total number of bytes input to this queue.

extremePortEgressRateLimitTable.name: extremePortEgressRateLimitTable
extremePortEgressRateLimitTable.description: Port egress rate limit statistics for a port.

extremePortEgressRateLimitType.name: extremePortEgressRateLimitType
extremePortEgressRateLimitType.description: The type of the current egress rate setting. A value of 1 signifies that the egress rate limit value is represented by a percentage of the maximum configurable port bandwidth. A value of 2 or 3 signifies the rate is configured in Kbps or Mbps respectively.

extremeWiredClientState.description: This attribute shall indicate the current state of the client. The attribute is enumerated as follows: 1 - Authenticated - client is authenticated. 2 - Unauthenticated - the client is connect but unauthenticated.

extremeWiredClientVLAN.name: extremeWiredClientVLAN
extremeWiredClientVLAN.description: This is the per-client VLAN which was pushed over by a RADIUS server or other mechanism.

extremeWiredClientPriority.name: extremeWiredClientPriority
extremeWiredClientPriority.description: This is a per-client 802.1p value which was either configured by the RADIUS server or statically through the port configuration table.

extremeWiredClientAuthType.name: extremeWiredClientAuthType
extremeWiredClientAuthType.description: This is an indication of what access method was used to authenticated the client.

extremeWiredClientLastStateChangeTime.name: extremeWiredClientLastStateChangeTime
extremeWiredClientLastStateChangeTime.description: This is the sysUpTime of the switch when the clients state changed last

extremeWiredClientIP.name: extremeWiredClientIP
extremeWiredClientIP.description: IP Address of the wired client.

extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearningEnabled.name: extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearningEnabled
extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearningEnabled.description: FDB Learning limit status. if it's enabled(1), switch limits the number of dynamically-learned MAC addresses per VLAN based on the extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearning Number. In case of disabled(0), switch allows to learn dynamic MAC addresses without limit.

extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearningNumber.name: extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearningNumber
extremePortVlanInfoLimitLearningNumber.description: Max Number of FDB Learning Limit. Specifies a limit on the number of MAC addresses that can be dynamically learned on the specific VLAN over port

extremePortVlanInfoMacLockDownEnabled.name: extremePortVlanInfoMacLockDownEnabled
extremePortVlanInfoMacLockDownEnabled.description: MAC Lock Down Status. If it's enabled(1), the current FDB entries is made performanent static, and no additional learning should be allowed. In case of disabled(0), port is unclocked to allow unlimiated and dynamic learning.
